<doc id="489745" wikidata="Q56537990" url="?curid=489745" title="Cherenkov">
<text>Cherenkov (sometimes spelled Čerenkov or Cerenkov) is a common Russian surname, which may refer to:

*Andrei Cherenkov (born 1976), Russian professional football manager and former player
*Andrew Cherenkov, a fictional character in the video game &quot;Xenosaga Episode I&quot;
*Fyodor Cherenkov (1959-2014), Soviet and Russian footballer
*Pavel Alekseyevich Cherenkov (1904–1990), Soviet physicist and a recipient of the Nobel Prize in physics in 1958

